PEERLESS BREAD MACHINE CO., Appellant, v. J. H. DAY COMPANY, Appellee. No. 7631. ■ Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. June 4, 1937. Allen & Allen, of Cincinnati, Ohio, for appellant. Frank L. Zugelter, of Cincinnati, Ohio, for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion by counsel for appellant, counsel for appellee consenting thereto, it is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that the appeal be and the same hereby is dismissed.
